Package: homestimator
Type: Package
Title: What the Package Does (Home range estimation)
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Jean de Dieu Tuyizere
Maintainer: The package maintainer <tuyizjado1994@gmail.com>
Description: More about what it does (the package estimates the habitat use by referring to kernel density estimator)
    It requires the installation of the following packages(sp, sf, ade4, adehabitatMA, CircStats, adehabitatLT, adehabitatHR).
    homestim(b, crs_n, y, x, unit_area, mo, ye).
    b is your file with (longitude, latitude, and groups)
    crs_n is the espg code.
    h is the bandwidth or smoothing parameter.
    p is the kernel density estimator probability (e.g., 50%, 90%, etc).
    unit_area is the unit that you want to have for your output area (km2, m2, etc).
    mo is the month for your data.
    ye is the year for your data.
